                <span class="nanny-section-label">Budgeting with confidence</span>
                <h2>What families should know before hiring a nanny</h2>
                <p>Understanding <strong>nanny cost in Dubai</strong> is not always straightforward because every household has different expectations. A family hiring a live-in nanny for daily childcare will budget differently from a family seeking a live-out nanny with school runs, after-school routines, travel support, or newborn experience. Costs can also vary depending on the candidate&rsquo;s background, references, experience with specific ages, language skills, flexibility, and the level of responsibility required in the home.</p>
                <p>For many families, the question is not only &ldquo;How much does a nanny cost?&rdquo; It is also whether the candidate is suitable, trustworthy, discreet, and able to work within the family&rsquo;s routine. A lower monthly cost may not represent good value if the placement is poorly matched. Likewise, a higher cost should be considered in relation to experience, stability, and the confidence a family feels when inviting someone into a private home.</p>
                <p>Trusted Household &amp; Childcare supports families with private, consultation-led introductions. If you are comparing <a href="/nanny-in-dubai">nanny in Dubai</a> options, our process helps you understand the type of candidate that may suit your household before reviewing suitable profiles.</p>
            </div>
            <aside class="nanny-intro-card" aria-label="Nanny cost factors">
                <h3>Main cost factors</h3>
