            <div class="nanny-faq-list">
                <details class="nanny-faq-item" open>
                    <summary>What is included in nanny cost in Dubai?</summary>
                    <p>The total cost may include monthly salary, living arrangement, transport, meals, visa or administrative responsibilities, insurance, leave, overtime, travel support, and any private introduction process fees.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="nanny-faq-item">
                    <summary>Does a live-in nanny cost less than a live-out nanny?</summary>
                    <p>Not always. A live-in nanny may receive accommodation and meals, while a live-out nanny may need transport or a higher salary expectation. The right comparison depends on the full arrangement.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="nanny-faq-item">
                    <summary>Why do experienced nannies cost more?</summary>
                    <p>Experienced nannies may bring stronger references, newborn or toddler knowledge, international household experience, language skills, travel flexibility, and greater confidence in daily routines.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="nanny-faq-item">
                    <summary>Can I discuss my nanny budget before reviewing candidates?</summary>
                    <p>Yes. We begin with a private consultation so families can discuss their expectations, schedule, and budget before reviewing suitable nanny candidates.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="nanny-faq-item">
                    <summary>Is the cheapest nanny option usually the best value?</summary>
                    <p>Not necessarily. Families should consider suitability, references, experience, communication, reliability, and long-term fit alongside monthly salary.</p>
                </details>
            </div>
        </section>

